      "text": ""
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Criteria 1 – APIs Availability"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This is based on \"from what core the service APIs shall be reachable“. From which below two cases are derived"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "-1a: Local service API’s (executable on one core only)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "-1b: Global (distributed /shared) service API’s (executable on any core)"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Criteria 2 - MCAL Kernel Execution Context"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Second criteria is about where the MCAL module Kernel shall reside to limit the side effects of collisions on busses and bridges due to concurrent access to HW peripherals from several cores."
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "-2a: One Local kernel (executable on one core only)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "-2b: Global (distributed /shared) kernel (executable on any core)"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Kernel is the core MCAL code which interacts with register and controller HW to perform the action"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "Criteria 3 - HW Elements Mapping"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "This is regarding “hardware capabilities in terms of mapping of HW peripherals to cores”, with this aspect the following cases are defined"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "-3a: One HW element mappable to one core only"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "-3b: One HW element mappable to several cores"
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "Example of HW mapping in Aurix with EB Tresos"
    },
